post.description:
Perform analysis on stage or store with specific tool and action
    <br>parametersString<br>
    string that contains a deserialized json of it.sealink.graphmodel.Models.SearchRequest
    {
        Parameters: {
            // filters for the search operation (if using charts saved on db)
            IncludeCharts: bool,
            ChartIds: string[],
            NodeFilter: null,
            IncludeNeighbours: bool,
            LinkFilter: null,
            IncludeEnds: bool,
            params: {
                async: "bool", // always false for GRAPH analyzer
                // KPaths params
                fromVertexId: "string" // starting entity id of the path for KPaths
                fromVertexType: "string", // starting entity type of the path for KPaths
                toVertexId: "string", // target entity id of the path for KPaths
                toVertexType: "string", // entity type of the path for KPaths
                depth: int // OPTIONAL, default 3 - depth of the path for KPaths 
            }
        },
        User: "string" // username of the current user
    }
    <br>dcj<br>
    file named dcj.json compressed in a zip file
